<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Defiant</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The scene is 'unreal' with slanted camera angle and slightly out of focus. It is Red alert and Worf is running with his bat'leth. A badly injured crewman reaches out for help. The bridge crew are dead. A group of Klingons are celebrating their victory. Worf enters the bridge to see dead Klingon children at the stations instead of Federation personnel.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Holding cell</td></tr>
<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Worf wakes from his nightmare.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>ODO:  Are you all right?</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>WORF:  What time is it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>ODO:  Oh four hundred. Your hearing starts in four hours. I suggest trying to get some sleep. You've got a big day ahead of you.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Wardroom</td></tr>
<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Admiral T'Lara (a Vulcan female) strikes the ship's bell six times.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>T'LARA:  This hearing will come to order. We are here to consider the request of the Klingon Empire that Lieutenant Commander Worf be extradited for trial on charges of murder. Advocate Ch'Pok, you may present your charges.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>CH'POK:  The Klingon Empire makes the following allegations against Lieutenant Commander Worf. That on Stardate 49648, while commanding the Starship Defiant, he knowingly fired upon and destroyed a Klingon civilian transport ship near the Pentath system. That as a result of that action, four hundred forty one Klingon civilians were killed. It is my intention to prove that Mister Worf was grossly negligent in his command of the Defiant. That his lust for combat overrode his good judgement. I ask only that he be returned to us to face the judgment of his own people. Thank you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>SISKO:  The Advocate neglected to mention in his opening statement that at the time in question, the Defiant was under attack by two Klingon warships. This was a combat situation with hundreds of lives at stake. It was at that moment, when suddenly the transport ship decloaked in front of the Defiant. Worf gave the order to fire, not because he was reckless or negligent, but because he believed he was firing on a warship. We intend to show that the destruction of the transport was a tragic, but unavoidable, accident.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>T'LARA:  I will hear formal evidence beginning tomorrow afternoon at fifteen hundred hours.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Promenade</td></tr>
<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>SISKO:  I want to know everything there is to know about the Klingon who was commanding that transport ship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>ODO:  You suspect that he wasn't just on an innocent passenger run.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>SISKO:  I'm going to argue that he saw the battle and then decided to join it. That he decloaked in order to attack the Defiant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>ODO:  Not the smartest decision he ever made.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>SISKO:  That's where you come in. Use your contacts in the Empire and find out something about this captain I can use. Was he reckless, did he have a reputation for drinking, did he have a death wish? Something.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>ODO:  I'll see what I can do.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Odo gets onto the turbolift.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Captain. (hands over a PADD) The witnesses I intend to call.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>SISKO:  Thank you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>CH'POK:  A remarkable station, Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>SISKO:  Thank you. We don't get many Klingon visitors anymore.</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>CH'POK:  After this case is over, you might be seeing a lot more of us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>SISKO:  Oh?</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>CH'POK:  When Worf is extradited, the Federation will be forced to admit that one of its officers committed a massacre. That will put you on the defensive throughout the quadrant. And while you're busy trying to repair a badly damaged reputation, we'll find ourselves with certain opportunities.</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>SISKO:  An opportunity to annex more Cardassian space and set up additional military bases in this sector?</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Possibly. But in any case, Worf is about to present us with something we never could have won in battle. Sympathy. Any move we make against you will be seen as a legitimate response to an outrageous slaughter.</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>SISKO:  You're presuming an awful lot. Worf maintains his innocence.</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>CH'POK:  And you are about to remind me that the burden of proof is mine. It's an interesting system of justice you have, Captain. It does have its flaws, however. It emphasises procedure over substance, form over fact.</td></tr>

<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>SISKO:  I'm sorry if you feel it puts you at a disadvantage.</td></tr>

<tr id="L30"><td><a href="#L30">30</a></td><td>CH'POK:  On the contrary. I look forward to fighting on your terms.</td></tr>

<tr id="L31"><td><a href="#L31">31</a></td><td>SISKO:  This is not a fight. It's the search for the truth.</td></tr>

<tr id="L32"><td><a href="#L32">32</a></td><td>CH'POK:  The truth must be won. I'll see you on the battlefield.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Wardroom</td></tr>
<tr id="L33"><td><a href="#L33">33</a></td><td>CH'POK:  I have studied Commander Worf's report, the Defiant's sensor logs, and the reports of the other officers on the Bridge. And I believe every word of it. It's a point of pride for the Federation that Starfleet officers never lie or commit fraud, so I will accept the facts of the case as they have been submitted.</td></tr>

<tr id="L34"><td><a href="#L34">34</a></td><td>SISKO:  Admiral, if there are no facts in dispute, then this hearing would appear to be at an end.</td></tr>

<tr id="L35"><td><a href="#L35">35</a></td><td>CH'POK:  We Klingons are not concerned with matters of fact and circumstance. What matters to us is what was in Worf's heart when he gave the order to fire. Was he just a Starfleet officer doing his duty or was he a Klingon warrior revelling in the battle? That is why I am here. Because if he was a Klingon lost in the bloodlust of combat, only we can judge him, not you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>SISKO:  We can't put a man's heart on trial. It's a subjective issue that cannot be reasoned in a court of law. I ask that the advocate be limited to arguing the evidence in this case.</td></tr>

<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Someone told me this was a search for the truth. Should we not follow that search wherever it takes us?</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>T'LARA:  The question of Commander Worf's motive is relevant. I will allow you to explore this issue, but only as far as logic permits.</td></tr>

<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>CH'POK:  I bow to your judgement.</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>T'LARA:  You may call your first witness.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The first witness is Dax.</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>CH'POK:  You're something of an expert on Klingon society, aren't you, Commander?</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>DAX:  My previous host, Curzon, would have called himself an expert. I tend to think of myself as having a passing familiarity with your culture.</td></tr>

<tr id="L44"><td><a href="#L44">44</a></td><td>CH'POK:  In your opinion, as someone with a passing familiarity with our culture, wouldn't you say the Klingons are a violent, warrior race?</td></tr>

<tr id="L45"><td><a href="#L45">45</a></td><td>DAX:  Yes, there is that aspect to your people.</td></tr>

<tr id="L46"><td><a href="#L46">46</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Would you agree that one of the things that makes a Klingon warrior so formidable is his predatory instinct, his bloodlust, if you will?</td></tr>

<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>DAX:  I'd agree with that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Now, when Worf was on the Defiant, engaged in combat, don't you think his predatory instinct took over?</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>DAX:  I think that instinct was present, but I've seen Mister Worf restrain it before.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>CH'POK:  How do you know so much about how he behaves in battle?</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>DAX:  In the holosuite. We've fought many times.</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>CH'POK:  You mean you practiced with Mister Worf. You played with him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>DAX:  Oh, no. When we fight, we fight.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Holosuite caves</td></tr>
<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: As she remembers a workout similar to that from Sons of Mogh</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>DAX [OC]:  I've made it very clear to Mister Worf that I never want him to take it easy on me because I'm a woman or a Trill.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Wardroom</td></tr>
<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Have you ever been injured?</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>DAX:  A few bruises here and there. A broken finger once. Nothing serious. And I've given him a few lumps of his own.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Holosuite caves</td></tr>
<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>CH'POK [OC]:  So you're not afraid of Mister Worf?</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Worf gets his blade against her neck.</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>DAX:  I'm no fool. I can see the killer instinct in his eyes, and I know he could kill me if he wants to. But that look always goes away. He knows when to stop. Ja'cht.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Wardroom</td></tr>
<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Admiral, at this time I would like to enter into evidence files I obtained from the defendant's private database this morning.</td></tr>

<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>SISKO:  Objection. There's been no search order issued for those files. This is a violation of Mister Worf's privacy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>T'LARA:  The captain is correct. Without a properly executed search order, or the permission of the defendant, any information you have accessed from his private database may not be admitted into evidence.</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>CH'POK:  Ah. I see. Well, I obviously have no search order, so I'll ask you, Worf. May I enter this files into evidence? Or do you have something to hide?</td></tr>

